    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Thanks for the PR! Can you give some guidelines as for reviewing every widget, what should we be looking for/paying attention to in those code changes?\r\n\r\nThis is a nice feature, with some good code addition, so releasing a beta and testing it out on multiple already existing websites is very important. So we get a sense of any issue that might happen.\r\n\r\nFor example, what happens if:\r\n- I am using urlSync and upgrade to the latest, will something break?\r\n- I developed a custom widget and now I will use routing, will something break?\r\n\r\nAlso worth considering:\r\n- Do we start deprecating urlSync in favour of routing?\r\n- If so, let's provide an easy upgrade guide for users of urlSync (link to doc from the code)\r\n\r\n> Find a place in the reference documentation\r\n\r\nI would put the reference into InstantSearch.js component doc if technically that's the easiest. Otherwise you'll have to create a specific page for an option of instantsearch(), maybe not easy. But keep it short in the component, and use the guide as a more complete way to create your own router.\r\n\r\nThen about creating your own router or using the feature, I would detail that in two guides, or one guide with two distinct sections:\r\n- routing\r\n  - usage\r\n  - advanced (more details on the API, semantics, behaviour)",
