  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Bugs found in http://disastrous-approval.surge.sh/:\r\n\r\n---\r\nPagination bug:\r\n- load\r\n- click on page 2\r\n- refresh\r\n- page 2 not selected and disappears from url\r\n\r\n---\r\nIndex selector bug:\r\n- load\r\n- change index to Lowest price\r\n- sortBy added to url\r\n- click on page 2\r\n- refresh\r\n- everything removed from url, selected index is lowest price still shown\r\n\r\nAlso if from there you change back the index to the \"default one\" (passed to instantsearch), now it's added to the url back\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nIndex selector bug 2:\r\n- load http://disastrous-approval.surge.sh/\r\n- select \"Lowest price\", it gets added to url\r\n- reload\r\n- select back \"most relevant\", it gets added to url\r\n- select back \"lowest price\", sortBy is removed to url\r\n- reload, index is now desync with what the user thought it was (edited)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nThis one ^ is very close to the previous one where everything gets removed from url (both page and index) so there might be just one bug in pagination and one in sortBy",
    "created_at": "2018-03-28T13:57:13Z",
